A nominated MCA in Kirinyaga has said he was attacked and injured by a member of the county assembly public service board.Speaking outside the assembly on Wednesday, George Kagori said Erick Muchina attacked him at the parking.He said Muchina hit him with a hard object in the face. Kagori reported the matter at the Kerugoya police station.He was treated at the Kerugoya Level Four Hospital and obtained a P3 form. A police officer at the Kerugoya station told the Star they are investigating the matter.Kagori said he may have been attacked for criticising Governor Joseph Ndathi&rsquo;s administration with five colleagues. Mutithi MCA Jinaro Njemumo said they will petition the assembly&rsquo;s Powers and Privileges Committee to sack Muchina.